rComments: Although Dr. Yee did explain the material well, I found the material for this course was not always presented in an organized or stimulating manner. He employs the use of presentations and group work a lot in PMU199, therefore it feels like I'm learning more from the students than from him.

The course material is poorly organized which makes is very diffifult to see where the focus is. Also, the marking machanism is try to grade the student as low as possible as Prof. Yee is looking for a word-to-word matched answer rather than conceptually correct answers.
